	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Celius wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">We'd have to minimize this, obviously. a 6x9 character would take 5400 different tiles according to that math</div>
<br />True, based on the upper bound of 54 tiles per frame. But a lot of the area of a character will be the blank tile, so I'll assume 32 to 42 tiles, which would fit 3 to 4 frames into each 2 KiB CHR page. So for a game with eight fighters, you'd have about 48 to 64 KiB of CHR per fighter, or the majority of a 512 KiB CHR ROM. But then Kart Fighter was half this because it used only about 2 frames per animation.
<br />
<br />But then the sheer amount of data also shows an advantage of a platform fighter over a Street Fighter style system. There's a reason that Street Fighter 2010 had nothing to do with Street Fighter.

		

		</td>
